  "Question": "<p>I am solving problems from an old exam (in topology, but I've translated the problem into more algebraic terms). The problem is the following:</p> <blockquote> <p>Let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_703\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a+b\\mathbb{Z}=\\{z\\in\\mathbb{Z}\\mid z=a+bk\\text{forsome}k\\in\\mathbb{Z}\\}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>a</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <mi>b</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo> <mrow> <mi>z</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>\u2223</mo> <mrow> <mi>z</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mi>a</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <mi>b</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>k</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\text</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>o</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>r</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>s</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>o</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>e</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>k</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> where <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_704\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a\\in\\mathbb{Z}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>a</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_705\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"b\\in\\mathbb{Z}-\\{0\\}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>b</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>. Suppose we have a collection of such sets   <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_706\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\{a_{i}+b_{i}\\mathbb{Z}\\mid i\\in\\mathbb{N}\\}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>a</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msub> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>b</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>\u2223</mo> <mrow> <mi>i</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>N</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo> </mrow> </math></span>   satisfying:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_707\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\bigcup_{i\\in\\mathbb{N}}(a_{i}+b_{i}\\mathbb{Z})=\\mathbb{Z}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <munder> <mo largeop=\"true\" mathsize=\"160%\" movablelimits=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u22c3</mo> <mrow> <mi>i</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>N</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </munder> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>a</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msub> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>b</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Show whether it is always possible to extract a finite   <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_708\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"I\\subset\\mathbb{N}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>I</mi> <mo>\u2282</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>N</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> s.t.</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_709\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\bigcup_{i\\in I}(a_{i}+b_{i}\\mathbb{Z})=\\mathbb{Z}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <munder> <mo largeop=\"true\" mathsize=\"160%\" movablelimits=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u22c3</mo> <mrow> <mi>i</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mi>I</mi> </mrow> </munder> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>a</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msub> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>b</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> </blockquote> <p>Unfortunately, I seem to have forgotten a lot of my elementary algebra... Nevertheless, I have attempted something:</p> <p>Let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_710\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\{p_{k}\\}=\\{2,3,5,\\dots\\}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msub> <mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>3</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>5</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> be the set of primes. We can construct: <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_711\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\left(\\bigcup_{k\\in\\mathbb{N}}(0+p_{k}\\mathbb{Z})\\right)\\cup(-1+\\ell_{1}%\n\\mathbb{Z})\\cup(1+\\ell_{2}\\mathbb{Z})=\\mathbb{Z}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <munder> <mo largeop=\"true\" mathsize=\"160%\" movablelimits=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u22c3</mo> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>N</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </munder> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u222a</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2113</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u222a</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2113</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>for some appropriate non-negative integers <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_712\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\ell_{1},\\ell_{2}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2113</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2113</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math></span>. We could for instance pick <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_713\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\ell_{1}=\\ell_{2}=5\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2113</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <msub> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2113</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mn>5</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. Suppose there is a finite sub-collection <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_714\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\{0+p_{k_{j}}\\}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mo>+</mo> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <msub> <mi>k</mi> <mi>j</mi> </msub> </msub> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo> </mrow> </math></span>, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_715\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"j=1,\\dots,n\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>j</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> s.t. </p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_716\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\left(\\bigcup_{1\\leq j\\leq n}(0+p_{k_{j}}\\mathbb{Z})\\right)\\cup(-1+5\\mathbb{Z}%\n)\\cup(1+5\\mathbb{Z})\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <munder> <mo largeop=\"true\" mathsize=\"160%\" movablelimits=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u22c3</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mi>j</mi> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </munder> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <msub> <mi>k</mi> <mi>j</mi> </msub> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u222a</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u222a</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Now, assume <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_717\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>p</mi> </math></span> is some prime s.t. <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_718\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?><math alttext=\"p&amp;gt;\\max\\{p_{k_{1}},\\dots,p_{k_{n}}\\}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>max</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msub><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></math></span>, then clearly <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_719\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p\\notin\\bigcup_{1\\leq j\\leq n}(0+p_{k_{j}}\\mathbb{Z})\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>p</mi> <mo>\u2209</mo> <mrow> <munder> <mo largeop=\"true\" mathsize=\"160%\" movablelimits=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u22c3</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mi>j</mi> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </munder> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <msub> <mi>k</mi> <mi>j</mi> </msub> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>. But here I run into a problem. I want <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_720\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p\\notin(-1+5\\mathbb{Z})\\cup(1+5\\mathbb{Z})\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>p</mi> <mo>\u2209</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u222a</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>. That is, I want <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_721\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"5\\nmid p-1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\nmid</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>p</mi> </mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_722\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"5\\nmid p+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\nmid</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>p</mi> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. This is of course possible if <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_723\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>p</mi> </math></span> is a prime with a <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_724\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"7\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>7</mn> </math></span> as its last digit. However, this approach means I have to prove that there are infinitely many primes ending on a <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_725\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"7\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>7</mn> </math></span>, which seems like a silly thing to prove for a simple problem like this. Surely, there is a nicer way of solving this?</p> <p><strong>EDIT</strong>: I am particularily interested in a solution not relying on topology, and whether a solution like my attempted solution works.</p>",
